caption: This place is a GEM! They are absolutely awesome and their lunch special is such an amazing deal. They are so incredibly kind and friendly. Their quality is top notch Please support this small business!

This is a little hidden gem in Elgin. Chris is amazing at what he can put on a plate and Mel is just the life of the restaurant and makes excellent cocktails. I am so happy they survived this pandemic! If you like good eating, please go and support them. You will NOT be disappointed! thank youu so much
The food is delicious here. The owner she knows how to make really delicious cocktails. Visited a lot before Covid and only doing take out now. Anyways love this spot.
When you're in Elgin, this the best sushi around. Always fresh and delicious.

If you're anywhere near Elgin, IL, and really looking for some great sushi - or other Japanese food - please check out Kobu! Immaculate fresh fish, wonderfully creative Maki rolls, delightful sauces and a vibrant atmosphere, overseen by a brother/sister team. Kris and Melody give the downtown Elgin scene a real boost!

We got the pork tonkatsu, the karaage, gyozas ginger salad, miso soup and I think 4 rolls. We also ordered 3 cocktails - the covid love spell which was perfection. We loved it all. I have to give Chris and his sister Melody a special thanks...they were so kind and patient guiding me. recommend
Best place around.

I got the lunch special- 2 roll sushi combo. It comes with the choices of sushi, miso soup and salad. The woman that took my order was super sweet, she asked if I wanted to add on an extra roll for 3 dollars. I said hell yeah I do ! I got the Philadelphia, spicy tuna and spicy himachi. I'm definitely going to be back!

Called early the other day to see if we could get delivery for dinner and the chef/owner Chris couldn't have been nicer. He was incredibly helpful and made great suggestions.  When I called back later in the day I spoke with his sister Melody and she is a delight.  The food was simply amazing and we will definitely be ordering again. Can't wait for them to totally open  up as we have a number of friends we want to take there. The food was fresh, delicious and definitely made with love. Tyou Kubo! Kubo!
Fantastic Sushi at a fare price. I have recommended Kubo to many of my friends and they were all very happy with their meals. I would defiantly recommend trying them if you haven't yet.

The food here is amazing.  I love their steak teriyaki and the sushi is delicious. However, it seems like they are always closed.  Today is like the third time I want to place an order an no one is answering the phone.  It’s Tuesday at 5:30pm.  Google shows they close at 8pm tonight.  If you are able to catch them open considered yourself lucky.
Great service great food! Great staff!
Fantastic place to have food when in a rush. Their customer service is quick, pricing is fair, fantastic vibes. Highly recommended

I've always had the freshest food here, very delicious. Before Covid when you could dine inside, service was great and now when I order take out it's still really good food and packaged well. I hope the best for you Kubo Sushi and you can make it through these hardships! I'll continue to support you and send others your way
Incredible food and cocktails! Staff and ambiance is top notch.
the food was super appetizing. next time i'll be back with my friends. it has an awesome atmosphere. ambience reminds me of colorado springs area.
We just ordered from there and I'm really happy the rolls were labeled.  Fast delivery, reasonable prices, and awesome signature rolls.

My experience here was just ok, after reading numerous reviews I thought it would be impressive but it was lack luster. I understand its tough with COVID restrictions but at least seem like you want business. I was really surprised with all the staff they had with so little tables. One of the waitresses was so drunk, I felt bad for anyone who owns this place. The guy making sushi seemed to be alright but he was really sporadic. I couldn't in good faith recommend this place to anyone. Food was 3 out of 5 service was 4 out of 5 but I think that's only because the girl was drunk and flirting with me. Cleanliness was 1 out of 5. I went to the restroom before leaving and it looked like they had not cleaned the bathrooms in weeks!! It was disgusting. Maybe I need to try it another time but it wont be any time soon. I also was going in there with a warning that the "owner" was a short tempered rude miserable person but they were no where in sight. I think this was in the beginning of October sometime.

I was reading the reviews yesterday and saw how everyone loved this place so I decided to order for the first time today. I must say I loved everything I got. I will definitely be ordering again soon since it’s close to my house. Can’t wait to go and eat at the sushi bar!
Only place I eat sushi in Elgin,  heck anyplace. Best service,  Medli, and Kris are great restaurant owners! Please forgive if I missed spelled your names!  Namaste!
Great place love this place!!! Go chef Kris!

So here we go again reviewing a place that I never thought I would. This place hands done on my kids gave me the absolute best culinary experience. Chef Kris is a absolute professional, the man put together a dish that a left to right direction like a book. Thank you man seriously good ownership and amazing food. Go Support!!!!!!!!
Our usual go to in Elgin. The best authentic and quality around.

Thank you so much! The food, the service, and the atmosphere was top notch! Wonderful owners (and gorgeous I may add 😉) were so nice to talk with us and explain the menu. My father who is a chef as well, is very picky, and he loved the food! We will be back very soon!!

last night was our first time in this magnificent restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening very much with the good service, with the magnificent  cuisine and booze and with the friendly charge. We will surely go back there in a short time.
Delicious sushi,  Diablo & Elginito rolls were so fresh
Amazing food and friendly people, I love this place. I'll be a regular for sure.

Many thanks to Kubo Sushi and Sake Lounge for a perfect anniversary dinner! I had "The Elginite", and my husband had the "Sushi Combo." We shared a soft shell crab appetizer, and we both had the miso soup and ginger salad. Everything, as usual, was delicious! We love this place!

Staff was friendly, establishment was super clean and the food was DELICIOUS! I highly recommend the miso soup. It has tons of flavor but is still light on the palate.

Your food never disappoints me! My favorite place to eat sushi and have drinks.
Great sushi, love their signature rolls.
I love that Elgin has a Delicious, Sushi spot right down town.  The food is prepared hot and fresh. Attentive service. Good Variety on the menu as well. The Kubo Bowl is a must Try.
I've gone here a times and I have never been disappointed! Sushi is always made fresh, service is always great! Here's "Under the Sea" it was so pretty, I almost felt guilty eating it!
They offer a fantastic variety of delicious food. I enjoy dining here. The employees are always very friendly, rates are convenient and the spot is always neat.

We arrived at this spot for dinner. we heard about this restaurant from a lot of people.  Well, it was a winning. The staff were extremely nice and we felt excellent. The meal was yummy. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. Warmly recommended.
Ramen, bento Box, everything is fresh and tasty here.

This place is my favorite site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. Awesome sushi, friendly staff. Your pallet will thank you! Ps try the sushi as it is before adding anything to it as it is already amazing.
Amazing food and people.

Great sushi, very nice stuff! I've been here 3 times and food was amazin!

My husband and I went right before the dinner rush. The staff was very prompt and attentive even after it started to get a little busier. The food was excellent. I tried their "Liquid Courage" cocktail and it was amazing. Jaime was our server and he was on point. This was the first time my husband and I ate at Kubo and it won't be our last.

Food is GREAT! Definitely try the Kubo Bowl & the Busheido Blade. The Bento Boxes are perfect for lunch. A little bit of everything. All are Both 10/10.  Customer service has always been excellent. We’ve been greeted promptly and treated friendly. I really love them and hope they continue to flourish and Elgin!

From the first moment  you enter this restaurant  the waiters give you a good feeling. Very courteous stuff, it is a nice place to  pass time with buddies or with your date. tasty  cuisine, skillful  chief cook and stuff, comfortable  cost and nice  service. Warmly recommended.

Best damn thing to come to downtown Elgin! The staff & owners are the absolute Bomdiggity!!! Food, Amazing!! 🤗 atmosphere, warm & inviting & good music 🎷 Prices reasonable! What more could you ask for?!!! Thank You Kuba for gracing downtown Elgin!! 🥰
Good service and the sushi is AMAZING...

I have never found a place on a whim with sushi this good. Owner is passionate. Staff is nice. Ingredients all seem good quality. I've had the chicken teriyaki, which has the sauce made from scratch. The place serves big portions and for reasonable rates. friendly staff members. I recommend this place.
Great food and service. Friendly staff.  Adventurous options as well as ‘safe’ food.

Didn’t know there was sushi right here in Elgin but I do now and I’ll be back for more.  We shared a fabulous tofu appetizer and had some nigiri and some rolls.  All was fresh and excellent.  Good beer and sake options and I couldn’t help but notice some very good looking cocktails passing by.  We had pre-gamed but next time i think we will order.  Great experience in Elgin!

Appetizing location to eat. Owner and other staff were very welcoming and polite.
Enjoyed dinner here on the 4th of July.  Everything was fresh and we enjoyed all the rolls and sashimi we ordered
Excellent meal at Kubo! Quality and Quantity are Fantastic! Skilled chef, friendly staff and fun location all make me want to come back.
Excellente food and the service absolutely great.

Pleasant hidden gem.  I came here looking for uni and was in for a treat.  Great fresh sashimi, and the uni shooters(not on the menu) were amazing! Thank you Chris and staff for an awesome experience.  My new sushi spot :)

Awesome place!

Went there as a pre Graduation lunch and it was great. Very friendly and great food.
Excellent, exceptional, amazing!!! Fantastic sushi and wonderful service! Really a great place!
Absolutely wonderful sushi.  Great service.
Really good sushi restaurant right in downtown Elgin. Loved my lunch! Looking forward to going back.
You have to try the Ramen bowl! Food is awesome, fresh, and oh so tasty. Staff is friendly, and atmosphere inviting. Why are you reading reviews instead of eating here right now??

Excellent, the owners are very friendly, brother and sister.  Sushi is some of the best and prices are very reasonable.  They have bar, table and booth sitting-smart concept.  We have been there two weekends in a row.  Try the Cubs home opener roll-White/Red Tuna, Shrimp tempura, etc. Excellent.  Fav new place.
Best ever

Beautiful presentation with delicious sushi rolls. There were a couple American twists to this Japanese style restaurant, which I thought we're all in good taste (pun intended). For instance there was a good selection of pallette cleansing  domestic beers. If you're into sushi I'd definitely recommend this place.
Love the atmosphere, food & drinks!
First time here today and I would totally go back. The service was outstanding and the food was delicious. Very friendly atmosphere.

I had placed an order to go for a bento box, I was very excited knowing I lived a short walk to a sushi restaurant, however when I returned home I realize that had forgotten some items so I had to call them to tell them i didn’t have them. They had them ready when I went back a second time but was disappointed that they didn’t check the bag to make sure I had everything before giving it to me when I had waited double the time told to me when I arrived there and ordered.
A friend and I stopped here after a casino run, just be chance, we happened to see it.  It was awesome, absolutely five star, all around great experience.

Oh my Deliciousness! My husband and I happened by this place on a lark! What a delightful surprise!! The sushi and sashimi were creative, so fresh, creatively artistic, but mostly super satisfying in texture, flavor and presentation. We’ve been experiencing sushi for over 30 years, and this place blows doors off most anything we’ve experienced! And in Elgin of all places. Worth the adventure. We are new loyals! Ask for the Tartar Pyramid and the Beni Toro! Delectable!

Had dinner at this sushi restaurant in downtown Elgin. Not one Japanese staff member in sight. Miso soup had a very strong chlorine taste, so I skipped that after one spoonful. I assume that it was prepared with local tap water, which is over-chlorinated. Soup may have been ok otherwise. Ordered the Sashimi platter and a Handroll. Both were nicely prepared,  but fish grade & selection werewere average quality. Sushi 3.5 stars, ambiance and side dishes 3.
Looking for great atmosphere? This was a gem hidden in downtown Elgin. Sushi and sashimi were phenomenal. Chris is an artist with a fish brush!
Very friendly staff, great environment and music.  Food was delicious and well priced.
Great sushi and desserts. Very fresh and  tasty selections on the menu. Friendly and knowledge staff.

Awesome experience today at this place. The chef even made me a roll that they didn't even have on the menu (spicy scallop). Really good fish, creative special rolls, and a nice atmosphere. Keep it up!!
This was a wonderful place to get amazing sushi!  The owners were great to meet and chat with!  I cant wait to come back to town and dine again!
Best sushi in the area! Mel is awesome and kris makes bomb rolls!

Fresh Ingredients, knowledgeable and friendly owners and staff, sleek and contemporary yet cozy and warm. Kubo hits all the marks and makes an incredible addition to the downtown Elgin food scene. 10 stars if it was an option!

I have traveled around the country and had sushi in many different cities. Most people won't even realize how luck Elgin is to have a sushi restaurant like this! This is the kind of place that can help Elgin become more of a destination. The freshness of the fish, especially being in the Midwest is not cheap. The prices however are extremely reasonable for the amount of fish you get. Mike is one of the owners and the sushi chef. He is good at what he does and seems to like to mix things up. This is my new favorite sushi spot. I just ate and already want to go back.
Great food!!!!
One of the best sushi places I’ve been to!
Best sushi/bento box I've come across.  The lighting was perfect and the music volume was just right!! The owners were great to talk to and our server Davalier was excellent.  We'll be coming back!
Loved everything we ordered.
Top notch service. Cute little restaurant, delicious food. Scarfed down the dragon roll before I could remember to take a picture. Will definitely come again!

I was shocked to see a sushi restaurant in my neighborhood so I had to try it.  I'm a little budget conscious, so I often go to "all you can eat" sushi restaurants.  This is not AYCE, so I was prepared to pay more than what I was used to.  With that being said, I think $12 for Sapporo on tap is too much.  I ordered without realizing the price, but that's my fault.  The presentation of the food was beautiful.  The appetizer (tartar pyramid - $13.75), my salad (seaweed salad $5.75), and my entree (sashimi app $12) were plated nicely.  The portion of the pyramid was a little small, but I thought the salad and sashimi app were appropriately sized for the price and quality.  The fish was very fresh.  No fishy smell in this restaurant.  If you ever walk into a restaurant that smells fishy - you probably don't want to order sushi.  The sashimi app is chef's choice and got 3 pieces each of tuna, salmon, yellowtail, and sea bass plated with daikon radish and shiso leaves.  I also want to mention that they serve white ginger, which I love.  The service was slow, but it's a new restaurant.  I'm sure the kinks are still being worked out and servers may still be new and/or training.  I will say that everyone is super nice here.  The hostess, our server, and the sushi chef were all very friendly.  Overall, I really enjoyed my food and the atmosphere.  I will be back and am excited to try other things on the menu.  They have a decent cocktail menu that I will certainly hit up next time I'm here.

I couldn't wait to try Kubo after reading an article about the owners long before they opened. WOW! It was worth the wait. I had the pleasure of meeting both owners, as they both work there and share their passion. It shows to. The decor, the quality of the food, the freshness and the authenticity as well.  I don't frequent too many Sushi places because after living in Japan, where I was first introduced to Sushi, it's just not the same thing here in the States. Well Kubo nails it. So glad they chose Elgin for this location. Besides delicious sushi, their Teriyaki Steak was simply outstanding as well as the Miso soup. So looking forward to trying the rest of the menu. I highly recommend Kubo .
It was fantastic and I recommend it to anyone. Had their Kubo roll that was great and a super white tuna special roll and was blown away try it.

I'm all for new businesses and I'm happy theres a place such as this closer to me so i Dont have to travel far for Ramen lol. Theres obviously room for improvent. The server was super nice , but since the place is new and everyone wants to try it, it does seem they may need at least one more person serving. We waited quite a while but the server made up for it , however most people wont be as understanding as us 😂 also the noodles in the ramen were a little too hard, thats something to work on, other than that no actual complaints. Goodluck & hope you guys do well
Good stuff.

Wonderful sushi!!!! The atmosphere is great, the music was awesome, and our server was so nice and took great care of us. We went on a Friday evening and it was PACKED so I do suggest you make a reservation before you go. Thankfully we made it before the rush, but I overheard them say the wait time was a half an hour. I am so pleased with our dining experience, and our sushi was truly a work of art!!!! Go here!!!!!
Great experience!! Beautiful ensamble! And food was amazing!
Incredible flavors! So fresh!! I’m in love 😍

You cant ask much more from a sushi restaurant. Great knowledgeable and friendly staff. The chef was amazing and showed me new flavors I never new possible. Great atmosphere and vibe. What an experience. Well done.

Been waiting to try and was not disappointed when I grabbed lunch. Stopped in to grab my pick up order and the lady was very nice and had me on my way with my food ASAP, very friendly service. They think of the little things, like separating the cold and hot food. Got back to the office and was taken back by how much differint stuff I got in my lunch bento box. Chicken teriyaki, rice, three rolls, salad, soup, and the sides. First things first, the sushi is the star but everything was great. The salad I felt meh about, likely because I'm not big on salad regardless of where it's from. Great food and service for sure!

I had been waiting to try this place for a long time now!! I work for the school district in Elgin so I have a lot of options for lunch if I want to go out the only thing is, it needs to be fast due to limited time. I got there around noon to place my order and wa wa s the door in 20 minutes!! I know it seems long but I did not call ahead for pick up. The food was out of this world!!! I had a ramen and a Kubo bowl and let me say, it was one of the most flavorful, elegant filling meals I have ever had!! The ramen was delightful as well but the bowl definitely took my little heart. Fresh salmon and tuna with squid salad, seaweed, ginger all on top of seasoned sushi rice. It was absolutely amazing!!! CAN NOT WAIT TO GO BACK!!!!!
Fantastic food! VERY generous portions and distinctively artistic presentation. Service and all staff members very friendly and professional. Treat you like family the moment you open the door.
The sushi was amazing!! We tried four different rolls and each melted in your mouth. Very fresh and delicious. Drinks were great too!!!
Nice atmosphere and Jazzy music, friendly/attentive staff, and fantastic sushi. Ordered "UP IN SMOKE" speciality roll potentially one of the best rolls I have had in Chicago land!

Fantastic fresh sushi and modern elegant setting. Sister and brother team, Melodi and Kris real know what theyre doing from the front and back of house to the carefully and wonderfully prepared dishes that are served. So glad Elgin finally has upscale sushi without being pretentious!!!
Excellent! Great service.  Great sushi

The chef is friendly and wants your experience to be enjoyable and informative. Throughout my lunch the chef told me where he got his fish and that he had gotten it that morning. The displays are beautiful and pleasing to the eye that not only is it delicious looking it is artfully designed and created with passion. His techniques are fluid to watch, much like a dance. Getting a seat at the bar will not only serve great food but also a show.  They serve miso soup and a ginger salad before the sushi.  Mind you, I do not like either of these things but this was a delight! Flavorful and fresh which I never had attributed those words to miso soup or ginger salad (which is usually drowned in ginger dressing) but not this! The sushi that followed only magnified the talent, passion, and sheer perfection this little sushi and sake lounge brings to Downtown Elgin!

I was really excited to have sushi in downtown Elgin. I was even more excited after trying the food, it's one of the best sushi's I've ever had. So far everything I've had here has been great! This will definitely be one of my go to places in the area.
